<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/24210</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-24"><hi rend="italic">September 24,
                                        1920</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With further reference to my letter of
                                June 18, 1920,<note n="20" xml:id="d188fn20">Not printed.</note>
                                relative to the presence in Mexican waters of a number of minor
                                naval units sent there during the month of April of this year, in
                                obedience to a request of the Department of State, I have the honor
                                to say that the emergency having passed, I am of the opinion that
                                these units may now, with safety, be withdrawn from Mexican
                                waters.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bainbridge
                                Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>